column6: I bought these in the Black Jacquard White design and I was so excited when they arrived (in a timely manner, typical Lulu fashion). However, when I tried them on, I was sad to see they did not feel like the other two pairs of Wunder-Unders I own. My go to line is usually the Aligns but I also like the WU's if they have some cool designs or colors. These were soft in the slightest, not that all the lulu's I own are soft rather than comfortable on the skin, these itched my legs so bad. Plus, I got them in my usual size, an 8, and the white dots look so stretched out and makes the pants not look right. I own an 8 in LITERALLY every pair of lulu's I own and have never had this problem-and no it is not thanks to recent weight gain as I got a pair of aligns around the same time and they fit beautifully. They were itchy, hard to get up my legs and kept falling throughout the day all the while giving me the camel-toe look. I am not sure what the difference is between these and the other WU's I have because I have never had this problem. First poor experience with Lulu leggings.

column6: I’d been gifted the Wunder Under High Rise in 28” and fell in love with how comfortable they were while keeping it all sucked in. The waistband doesn’t roll down, and these 7/8 are great for me at 5’2”. I did feel these were SLIGHTLY more snug than the solid black 28” ones. I ordered the 25” Wunder Under Luon in black and also find these to be slightly looser than this version. Overall, anything Wunder Under is amazingly comfortable for a legging, and I was surprised they weren’t too thin for wearing to and fro during and Illinois winter yet not too warm for an indoor run in the gym.

I originally got a size 6. They fit great at first but then stretched out after one wash and wear. I was hiking them up non stop. I contacted lululemon and they let me return so that I could get a size 4. Thank you so much lululemon! Great customer service! If you’re having a difficult time deciding on a size, I recommend getting the smaller. They may feel really tight at first but trust me! That’s what you want! For reference, I’m 5’4 128 lbs and a 4 is perfect. These are the best leggings you can get!

column5: Not as good as my old pair
column6: I bought these because I have an old pair of luon high times pants that I LOVE and have worn to near death. However, this pair is a far cry from the former quality I expect from Lululemon. They are not soft at all and the fabric feels thinner and less sturdy than I am used to. I wish you would make them like you used to!

All I have from lulu are dark colors, mostly black. I wanted a new pattern/pair to stand out when I wore them and these are perfect! They are so comfortable and I have gotten so many compliments on them. I don’t wear them to workout because the wunder unders aren’t my favorite for workout gear.

I am both curvy and muscular and have a hard time finding leggings that are flattering on me and stay up above my hips. These leggings are perfect! High rise makes sure they don't slip down at all while working out and the fabric is thick enough to make me feel "held in" without being too hot. The patterns are handy too as they don't get that stretched out look over some potentially wider areas of your legs (my thighs and calves). Very slimming!
These pants are SO see through I can’t believe I paid $98 for these glad I did get the opportunity to exchange these for navy pants do not get light colored pants from lulu

I ordered 2 pair of these pants in different colors and they fit totally different. I looked at the tags and one says 45% polyester,42% nylon,13% elastane and the other is 78% Nylon,22% Lycra elastane. If I order 2 pairs of pants both marked “Luon” I expect them to be the same. I understand you have a wide variety of fabrics and even several different kinds of Luon (full on Luon, etc.) but these pants are all marked “Luon” so the fit and make-up of the fabric should be the SAME! Consistency is not too much to ask for pants in this price range. I tried texting with a representative and she had no clue what I was even talking about. She didn’t even know the difference in the fabrics- which I learned by reading on lthe website. So I went to the store and they didn’t know either! I’m really frustrated at this point. I can try to order another pair but who knows what I’ll get!!!!!

column6: I have a few pairs of these that I've bought over the years that Il love. They're thicker w/ compression, so they hold everything in. I also have a few pairs of the Align, which I absolutely love too, but they're too thin for the fall and winter. I ordered the blue w/ white dots bc I wanted another thicker pair w/ compression for the cooler weather. The fabric is SO different, luxtreme like, which I hate. It was loose around the waist, the material was super thin, and it was scratchy as well. Not the usual soft LLL quality that I was expecting. I feel like the material varies from pant to pant. I sent them back because I thought they were quite disappointing. I wish there was more consistency with the fabrics. If they're thick, separate them into another category from the thin ones. It's like I'm rolling dice for my pants. You really don't know what you're going to get.

The leggings are well made, they don't offer tons of compression, so there is some give and stretch, idea for HIIT or yoga. There was no pilling, no lose strings, and most importantly they were squat proof because i actually squatted in them. The color scheme is very nice and more on the subtle side pattern wise. I would highly recommend these especially if you like high waisted leggings and are active or just lounging around (pretty expensive for just lounging IMO). I wish they came in more colors and interesting stitching, but not wild and difficult colors to wear.

column6: This review is specifically for the Wee Are From Space Nimbus Battleship. Normally, I love high rise wunder unders, but not so much this pair and I will be returning. They are completely sheer, even when just standing upright. I don't mind a little bit of sheerness when in a deep squat or bending over, but if you can see the color my skin through the pant when standing upright, that's not good.

I bought these leggings in Wee Are From Space Nimbus Battleship a little over a month ago and am shocked by the poor quality. I have thick thighs, so I'm used to some pilling in the crotch area, but in all my other pairs of leggings from here, the pilling wouldn't appear until months after wearing them weekly. With these though, I noticed pilling after my second time wearing them -- I had only been wearing them on errands, not even at the gym! I have leggings from Lululemon that I bought 3 years ago and have the same amount of pilling as these 1-1/2 month old leggings.
In addition, I have other light grey/white Wunder Under leggings and have never had issues with them being see-through -- I can wear neon pink or black underwear without it showing through. With these new leggings, I initially noticed that I had to wear nude underwear with them, which is fine as that is to be expected with nearly white leggings, but last week I noticed when I bent over in front of a mirror that I could clearly see my butt through the leggings.
Maybe I got a dud pair, but regardless the quality of Lululemon clothing is quickly going downhill. Unfortunately, I think this will be the last time I buy leggings from here.

column6: Very comfortable tights, but did not last very long for me :/ The material is nice and soft but still breathable. I would say they are an in between of my aligns that are more buttery but also not as durable and the basic full on luon wunder under which are more compressive but also thicker material. I loved these in my 'Wee Are From Space Ice Grey Alpine White' color (but warning they are slightly see through with very vibrant underwear) and they quickly were one of my favorite lulu pants especially for days where I am running errands before the gym but sadly they stretched out on me. I wash all my lululemon clothes with their specific instructions including air drying them and after the first wash I noticed them getting looser in the waist band and now if I wear them during a HIIT workout I have to constantly pull them up. I loved how comfortable they were but wish they didn't stretch out so fast :(
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey mandy112,\nThanks for taking the time to reach out today. We stand behind the quality of our gear and are sorry to hear your gear isn't performing. Give our GEC a call at 1.877.263.9300 so they can follow up and chat.", 'LL_response_date': 'January 15, 2018'}

column5: Bummed about the fabric's resiliency, cut is cute
column6: I have been wearing wunder unders for many years and with my latest pair of all blacks feel that the quality of fabric is becoming rough and isn't holding its luster after washing them only 3 times (in cold, hang dry) Feel that the luster and hold of the fabric is the best part about wunder unders (usually) but not with this particular pair. Will be more cautious if buying them again. I do love the 7/8 cut as a shorter lady.

Please keep an eye on your inbox as I’ll be reaching out shortly to connect and get to work on a solution for you.", 'LL_response_date': 'January 15, 2018'}

column6: This is my second pair of Lulu leggings that I have purchased. The first pair (align) the company refunded me because they were pulling after 3 wears, with no wash inbeetween. ( I have to say lululemon has the best customer service. ) So I decided to try the wunder under, and well.... same expierence, they are already pilling, but the good thing is, is that they are dark so you can’t tell. The material is very comfortable, something I could wear during winter, it almost reminds me of fleece lined leggings. They work great for working out because there is no chance anyone can see your behind, which is necessary when going to the gym! I do not have to constantly pull the up, they stay in place very nicely. The only thing I can recommend to lulu, is If you make leggings over $100, the least they could do isn’t not pile. I’ve bought leggings from cheap retail stores that have lasted years, and still look good. But other than that I like them, It’s a must to hand wash!

I loved these when I picked them out, but after wearing them a few times they started to pill in the crotch area. This has never happened before when buying leggings from Lulu, but this is really disappointing as I've bought nearly $800 worth of Lulu this year and two pairs of these are pilling after a few wears. So bummed!

column6: I used to love these leggings but after a few washes (the way lululemon is supposed to) they fall apart. They are super loose now and I feel like I'm always pulling them up.... super annoying.

column6: I bought these pants in the 'Wee Are From Space Ice Grey Alpine White' color and they sooo cute and soft. Soft as in cottony dream soft. After reading the reviews, I wasn't 100% confident in buying them but once I felt them in-store I was instantly obsessed. I'm super happy and I find they fit true to Lulu sizing! These pair perfectly with my all white define jacket!

column5: Best leggings I own from Lululemon
column6: This are great pants! I am 5'4 with short legs and I always buy 7/8 pants that hit me right at the ankle and don't have to get them hemmed, just easier! I love the feel of this fabric too!

I bought these pants in the color Warp Speed Filtered Orange Electric Coral, simply because I loved the pattern. However, when they arrived, I tried them on and the fabric was awful! It's itchy, scratchy, stiff, and see through! I love wunder unders, but this experience will sure make me go into the store instead of ordering online. I do not recommend these pants (in that specific color) to anyone. Lululemon is my favorite brand of all time and I am extremely disappointed in the quality and fit of these pants. I ordered my regular size (4) and they were so tight and not stretchy at all. :(

I bought these pants last February as a birthday gift for my daughter. The fabric pilled and they even have a small hole in them. She is asking for a new pair for Christmas, but I am hesitant to spend another $98 especially after seeing some of the other reviews sharing the same experience. I have bought many other high end brands that have held up much better, very disappointed it the quality for the price.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hi MyaP,\nThank you for reaching out and sharing your feedback and concerns about your Wunder Under Hi-Rise 7/8 Tight with us. Please stop by your local store or call our Guest Education Centre at 1.877.263.9300 and we will go over some options so we can find a solve that makes you happy.', 'LL_response_date': 'December 11, 2017'}

column5: Disappointing Fabric in Orange Coral Color
column6: I originally bought the heathered gray color of these pants when I was pregnant for a nice high waisted, forgiving pair of pants while practicing high intensity yoga and loved them. I recently bought a second pair of these pants after having my baby because I wore the ones I had during my pregnancy so much. The original pair fit the whole time I was pregnant and I still wear them after. I loved the material, not too tight, not too loose, retained shape, really comfortable, and flattering. I recently bought what I thought was the same exact pair of pants post baby, but the fabric is totally different. I think maybe because of the color? I got the Warp Speed Filtered Orange Coral color and the material is the worst Lulu fabric I have come across. It isn't very stretchy and doesn't retain shape very well. Also, the color is way more pink in person that on the website. Most disappointing Lulu item I own.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey DoStuff,\nOh dear. Thanks for taking the time to share this feedback with us- we always want to ensure that our gear is performing for you as intended, and will be sending you an email so we can chat further.', 'LL_response_date': 'December 1, 2017'}

column6: I bought these a couple of weeks ago and completely loved them but then after I had worn them only a few times, I noticed a lot of pilling in the thigh area and a tear right by it. I'm just very disappointed that they tore.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey dasovica,\nThank you for taking the time to connect with us. Pilling is definitely not what we like to hear, and making things right for you is our priority. Keep an eye on your inbox—I'm sending you an email to chat more.", 'LL_response_date': 'November 30, 2017'}

column5: LOVE the fabric (NOT full on anything, simply Luon)
column6: Absolutely love these because the fabric is different and not like compression fabric. I got the wee are from space white/gray and they are amazing. They fit perfectly, not too loose and not too tight (DEF not too tight), but still hugging so you are silhouetted! I have probably 25+ pairs of the Align pants and these fit somewhat more like those instead of the "full-on" wunder unders. If you want something tighter then go with either "full-on luxtreme or luon", or size down! Those will fit tighter.

I recently bought these in the wee are from space ice grey alpine color. While they looked cute and felt warm, I experienced lots of pilling in the inner thigh region after just a few hours of wear. I haven't experienced this with my other lulu leggings, and was very disappointed in the fabric these leggings are made of.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hi Panda2700,\nThanks so much for sharing your thoughts today. We stand behind the quality of our gear and will be in touch shortly via email to follow up and help!', 'LL_response_date': 'November 29, 2017'}

column6: bought the camp black and white ands absolutely love them, then I bought the orange electric and they have stretched to the point where I can't keep them up!! whats going on? I miss the old Lulu leggings that actually fit the body perfectly! very unsatisfied.

column6: I own a lot of lulu leggings, however I have found these to already start to pill and I bought them two weeks ago. After one or two washes they began to pill pretty badly. I have another pair of the Wunder Under leggings and haven't had a problem with them or had them pill this much.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey Runner104,\nThanks so much for sharing your thoughts today. We stand behind the quality of our gear and will be in touch shortly via email to follow up and help!\nChat soon.', 'LL_response_date': 'November 9, 2017'}

column5: Frayed camo black and white not see through for me
column6:
I got the frayed camo black and white and they are definitely not see through for me. I even sized down because I wanted a more hugged sensation; this type of material has a lot of stretch, but I did multiple checks with my husband in various lighting and they weren't see through. The quality may differ from pair to pair, so I would try on in store to purchase.
By the way I also tried on space dye coral pattern and that material was way more stretchy, so I wouldn't get those if you like the tighter feel. Also, the coral looked a bit like a Halloween design to me. Maybe because Halloween is on my mind right now, but just thought I'd mention it.

After about 5 washes they are pilling really bad. I only wash my lulu stuff with other lulu items, on cold, with special detergent. I have a few wunder under's but they have never pilled this bad. I understand some pilling is unavoidable, which is okay but these pants look and feel awful after washing and wearing. This pant also seems tighter than previous wunder under's and makes for an uncomfortable wear. Pretty disappointed with lulu's quality in these pants. I wish they would make each wunder under the same fit.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey Chelseamc,\nWe hear your disappointment and will be sending an email your way to follow up and lend a helping hand.\nSpeak soon.', 'LL_response_date': 'October 23, 2017'}

column6:
I wore these pants as soon as I got them to teach two classes - kickboxing and cycle. They were fine at first, but continued to stretch out as I moved. By the time I taught my second class, the waistband was so loose that I was constantly pulling them up. They never bounced back to their original fit like lulu usually does. I'm between sizes so I even ordered the smaller size, but they still stretched out a lot and were not super comfortable to wear. I was hoping they would fit like regular wonderunders, but they're a different material that's not super great. I got these in the "luon warp speed filtered orange electric coral" and was super excited about some space dye. Turns out they're more of a pink color when in the picture they look black and white.
Pretty disappointed in these pants. Stick with regular wonders, not the specialty ones.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey sweatyhk,\nThanks for taking the time to share your feedback. We would love to get a bit more information on your experience, and look into some options. An email is headed your way, so keep an eye out.', 'LL_response_date': 'October 19, 2017'}

column5: so comfortable but the waist band is kind of loose.
column6: I absolutely love these, they are so comfortable. The only issue I have is I'm constantly adjusting the waist bad. I feel it should be a little tighter. other than that they are perfect!

Recently bought these in the frayed camo black and white and I was SO excited. Instantly fell in love UNTIL I was kindly pulled aside after a barre class and told that my $98 leggings were in fact SEE THROUGH when I bent over... Very disappointed
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hi SweatyLiving,\nOh dear—that's a thumbs down from us. I’d love to lend a hand with some solutions so I’ve sent you an email that outlines the next steps. Chat soon!", 'LL_response_date': 'October 16, 2017'}

column6: So obsessed with these tights! They are PERFECT. So comfortable that I plan on buying them in every pattern Lulu makes! The material feels so durable and cottony soft and I seriously never want to take these tights off. Best Lulu purchase I have ever made. I wear a 4 in the Aligns and Fast & Free Tights and I wear a 6 in my Wunder Under Full-On Luxtreme Tights and I ordered a 6 in these and they fit perfect!

Purchased these in the print Nimbus Battleship and Ice Grey Alpine White. The only problem I have is why I didn't purchase more back ups! I'm not sure why there are bad reviews on this product because it's great! True to size, I always order a size 2 in all of my leggings and have never had a problem with these being see through. They're one of the comfiest pants I own next to the Align Pant. The waist band never rolls down on me during my work outs and I've never had a problem with having to constantly pull them up. They stay in place all day and they retain their shape even after washing. Never had a problem with pilling. Doesn't show sweat as well even with how light the color and material is! Purchased my second pair of the Ice Grey Alpine White and my old pair from a year ago looks exactly like the new pair I now own. Bummed that I didn't purchase 2 of the Nimbus Battleship when it was in stock but I definitely will next time they come back again. I definitely recommend this!

This was my 1st purchase at Lululemon and a complete splurge. I was very excited and ended up getting 2 pairs. However, they excitement was short lived. I have now worn both pairs twice and am constantly pulling them up and adjusting them during class and when just walking. Very frustrated that I splurged and now have buyers remorse.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey Kayon,\nWe're sorry to hear you're experiencing retention loss with your Wunder Under Hi-Rise 7/8. We would love to get a better understanding why you may be experiencing this. We have sent you an email to have a further chat.", 'LL_response_date': 'September 20, 2017'}

column5: Very comfortable with one big problem!
column6: I'm a first time Lulu buyer and was very excited to try their workout leggings, as my friends have raved about them for some time. I have to say, they are very comfortable! They were easy to move in and the waist band did not cut into my skin. However, this SPECIFIC COLOR is NOT suitable for working out in a gym. During my workout, I noticed that my leggings were showing ALL sweat stains. It was actually quite embarrassing. My shirt luckily was a bit longer, so I was able to hide some stains. Unfortunately, these expensive leggings cannot be worn in the gym, I can only wear them around the house etc. i was quite disappointed since the whole point of buying Lulu is that you are buying top quality workout gear.

column5: Loved at first, now disappointed in quality
column6: Loved these 7/8 pants for the first couple months, now I've noticed they've began pilling and are now rough material. I'm disappointed in the quality because I take such great care of my lulus and wash them separately from other materials. If they didn't pill/become rough, they would be my favorite 7/8 pants!
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey JustineAlyssa,\nThanks for taking the time to reach out today. We stand behind the quality of our gear and are sorry to hear your gear isn't performing. Give our GEC a call at 1.877.263.9300 so they can follow up and chat.", 'LL_response_date': 'July 20, 2017'}

column6: I recently purchased these leggings as I was obsessed with the pattern! I purchased them in my regular size and found that they stretched out during my first wear and was really disappointed. These leggings are an investment so it is a bit frustrating when they don't work out. I would recommend this item as the pattern is so versatile, however I would recommend you size down.

column6: I honestly love these leggings. They are the perfect length for me (5'6") and they are so comfortable. However, for being about a hundred bucks they are kind of sheer, I can see the white tag on the back through the leggings and I've worn them only once at home and I've already noticed multiple loose threads. Wish these had better quality for being lululemon.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey Michelleeey,\nThanks so much for sharing your thoughts today. We stand behind the quality of our gear and will be in touch shortly via email to follow up and help!\nChat soon.', 'LL_response_date': 'July 12, 2017'}

column6: The Luon material used for these is suuuuper soft. These are obviously tights with a "hugged in" sensation but because the material is softer, there is less of a "compression" feel. To those reviews who complain that these lost their tension, I would recommend going a size down. Most stretch garments relax a little over a few wears so to maintain the snug feeling with these just size down. They might be a little tight at first but they will relax and be the perfect amount of support. There are no hard seams around the waistband so sizing down wont cause a smaller waist seam to dig in. I am in love with these tights in the We are From Space Nimbus Battleship color.

column5: Lost Compression.. really wanted to love these!
column6: I'm really sad about these!!! I was so excited to get these when I ordered them, perfect for the gym and lounging! Unfortunately after a day of wearing them they lost all the compression and not longer fit.. They're too big and have "saggy bum". I wouldn't recommend these leggings to anyone for that reason. I don't enjoy having to pull up my pants every 5 mins when I'm walking. For the look these are amazing, unfortunately the sizing and the compression are very disappointing.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey GymLover1313,\nWe hear your disappointment with the retention loss on your gear and will be sending an email your way to help.\nChat with you soon.', 'LL_response_date': 'May 15, 2017'}

column5: Usually love this style, but these are a bummer
column6: I grabbed these High Times when I could finally get my hands on the white print at the end of last summer. I loved the look, and the only thing I worried about initially was whether or not they would be see-through! And they're not!! BUT, I did see after about 3 wears that they stretch out a ridiculous amount. I've never experienced this with any of my other High Times, and I'm in R&D so I'm constantly trying out all the Lulu pants. I take really great care of these pants-- washing them on a cold, delicate cycle, w/o fabric softener, and only with other Lulu products. Hang them to dry of course. I'm so frustrated with these pants, and they really were my favorite, and they still are for the first 45 minutes of each wear before they're a stretched-out, baggy mess.

We stand behind the quality of our gear and if our gear doesn't perform for you - we'd love to help you out. An email is coming your way so we can follow up and help.", 'LL_response_date': 'May 14, 2017'}

column6: I purchased these in wee are from space nimbus battleship and I was so excited to get them in as I LOVE the print (I have it in other items). However, it is completely see through! I considered keeping them for just around the house, but couldn't justify the price for that. I am so sad, but had to return. They were true to size, but not as "tight" as my other wunder unders that have the same "hugged" fit. I also agree with another reviewer that they were a little loose in the ankles and I haven't had that problem before in this pant.

I’m actually a new customer of Lululemon. After falling in love with Lululemon’s On The Fly line ( I bought 3 pairs of them), I decided to try new things and got a pair of leggings for my after work yoga classes. The person who was helping me in the store recommended Wunder under 7/8. When I tried it on in the store it felt great. However, after wearing them for a couple of hours today I realized that the waist line ROLLS down crazy! (I am 5' 5" and 140lbs) Every time I sit down it rolls down... I guess I’ll be spending most of my day rolling them back up... So DISAPPOINTED! All I wanted was a simple pair of black leggings for yoga... So SAD :( I won’t be going back to Lululemon for a while; I was more satisfied with Lucy’s leggings.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey GoYoga,\nSorry to hear that your Wunder Under Hi-Rise 7/8 isn't holding up as expected. We stand behind the quality of our gear and have sent an email your way to discuss this further, and look into our options.", 'LL_response_date': 'May 6, 2017'}

column6: I bought these in the wee are from space nimbus battleship style and love them. Wore them for today's workout and they felt so soft as if I was not wearing pants. Another positive I love is the waistband because it's high rise but keeps everything in. Other high waisted pants I have, usually have a thick band which I feel makes me larger than I am but did not have that problem with these pants.

I have the arrow patterned print. First of all, the print is gorgeous and I love the textured feel. These pants are soft, comfy and flattering. My dream yoga pants. They are also pilling less than usual in the crotch area (I'm pretty sure all pants from all brands pill here in non-slick materials), which is a major plus. I haven't noticed any sheerness in this colorway. The ankles are nice and tight on me despite the fact that the 28' length is still too long (love my 25' haha). More of these for sure <3

They could be great... but are a little sheer for me. Defiantly too expensive to keep them. I have set up a return for them. The ankles are loose on me as well. Bummed about the pants because the material does seem to be great.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hi May2198,\nOh dear, I'm sorry to hear that your pants are sheer, that's not what we like to hear. I'm sending you an email to chat more and work out a resolution. Chat with you soon.", 'LL_response_date': 'May 1, 2017'}

column6: The material of these are soooo amazing. Comfortable, yet flattering pair of pants. They should definitely make more of this specific fit. These run true to size. I could literally live in these pants...make more colors please!!! :)

column5: So pretty but kind of see through :(
column6: I debated ordering these for so long and finally got them but unfortunately they're also see through. I really wouldn't mind keeping them because its not a huge issue but I just can't justify a hundred dollar pair of pants that are see through. The print is gorgeous, the fit is hugged, and the material is so soft, but also kinda of thin feeling and I couldn't imagine they'd hold up for years of wear and washing which I expect lulu to. Probably going to return as much as I don't want to. Ankles also kind of loose, but that isn't an issue for me.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey jlk167,\nWe're sorry to hear your disappointment with the coverage issues you’re experiencing with your Wunder Under Hi-Rise 7/8 Tight. An email is headed your way so we can follow up and lend a hand—chat soon.", 'LL_response_date': 'April 27, 2017'}

column6:
I was quickly browsing for a new pair of leggings and I was very excited to see these when I was browsing through the Wunder Under stack. They are a unique color that I haven't seen before. Unfortunately, I did not know they were a modification on the High Times pant. Had I known, I would not have purchased them. I LOVE lulu, especially the "hugged" sensation the Wunder Under give. I have at least 5 pair that I wear to both teach and exercise in. I also have a pair of High Times that just aren't my favorite because of their lack of compression.
Just a fair warning to anyone who is particular about their leggings like I am - these are not a "hugged" feeling like the tag reads.

I bought these 7/8 Wunder Unders and another pair of regular length crops (still Wunder Unders), but am so so so disappointed with these :( The 7/8 length is so awkward and weird...I'm sure it looks better on tall people, but I'm 5'3 and these just look ridiculous.
I bought these to teach spin in and not only do they fall down/bunch up at the waist (even though they're high rise), the awkward length on my ankle slightly above the ankle) bunches up when I stand and run on the bike... ALSO another thing that is seriously annoying is they PILL!! When I bought these, I specifically told the girl helping me in the store that I teach spin, need pants that will hold up on the bike, etc. She assured me these were the way to go...nope. I'm hoping these were just one pair that didn't work for me, and hopefully my next pair (not these same ones) will be much better.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hi runner22,\nThanks for reaching out and sharing your valuable feedback with us. Quality is at the heart of our gear and we're eager to turn things around, so stand by—an email is coming your way soon.", 'LL_response_date': 'April 24, 2017'}

column5: do not pass the squat test
column6: contrary to other reviewers, i experienced see-through issues with these when doing the "squat test." when i first put them on, my immediate thought was, "wow, these are super soft and comfy, could probably even use a size down in these because they feel a little big esp in the waist." however, when i did the squat test i could see straight through these in the mirror. yeah, sure, you can wear nude colored undies and that would prob solve the issue, but i rather not have a garment that i HAVE to wear nude colored unmentionables with if you know what i mean. i do like the cut of these pants a lot, and actually do prefer them to the high times pant (my second favorite lulu pant after aligns - ankles on these are tighter as mentioned by another reviewer, and the waist seems a little less high), but i happen to have these in the EXACT same colorway (wee are from space nimbus battleship) in the high times pant (i never actually wore them so they still have the tags lol), and those do pass the squat test in the same size. i will say that the high times ones are not as soft as these, but they fit tighter through the hip, etc., so one would think that if anything those would be the ones with the transparency issue?! any who, while these pants have an awesome cut and are super comfy, i will be returning them since i do not wish to be constrained by underwear color choice whenever i wear them (and i have the same color in a similar pant that i don't have that issue with).
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Hey MacanS,\nThanks for taking the time to get in touch. We stand behind the quality of our gear and will be sending an email your way to lend a helping hand.\nChat soon.', 'LL_response_date': 'April 22, 2017'}

column6: These are by leaps and bounds my favorite pair of Lulu leggings. I'm 5'4 and 135 lbs and the size 4 fits perfectly. I did size down from my usual size as my normal 6 was pretty loose in the calf and ankle. These are seriously amazing. They are the first pair I wear after laundry every single time. They don't show sweat, and are amazing even for lounging and wearing out and about. Now that they come in a second color I'm going to have to order another pair! Not see through, don't show sweat, so flattering, well done lululemon!!!

These have got to be my favorite leggings from lulu. They are so freaking soft and comfortable. They do fall down a bit during activity and I wouldn't say they are completely opaque, but none the less they are the best!

These pants are AMAZING! These are hands down my favorite lulu pants. They nailed it with these. They are TTS (5'2, 120 pounds). I ordered both pairs because they are super flattering. They are not see through nor do they look worn after 5 washes. They are super soft and comfy. The seams do not dig and they do not ride up where you constantly have to pull them up. I could go on, but you get the point. Must buy!

Just got these pants in the new print and love them! Unlike the high times, the ankles on these pants are nice and tight! WIN! Ordered my usual size 4 and they are spot on. Also got the matching energy bra in size 8, really cute outfit. Finally some good prints and a good fit from lululemon.
